observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant and the Acting Property/Supply Officer to continue their efforts to reconcile and determine the nature of discrepancies noted in the PPE account and make the necessary adjustments/corrections, considering all possible remedies to address the negative observations and problems encountered in the conduct of physical inventory. Specifically, the Acting Property Officer should ensure that:
a. Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) and/or Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR) are issued for all PPE items.
b. issued PPE items are returned to the Property Office before the issuance of Agency Clearance for those officials and employees who will apply for retirement and/or transfer of office;
c. demolished constructed buildings, road networks and other infrastructure assets are inventoried and requested to be dropped from the books;
d. unserviceable equipment which are already disposed are dropped from the books of account;
e. proper turnover of PPE items from outgoing to incoming officials are observed/made;
f. donated properties are properly documented and covered by Deeds of Donation and Acceptance of Donations;
g. extra efforts are exerted to trace records of all PPE items. We further recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Acting Property Officer to facilitate the disposal of unserviceable motor vehicles and other properties found unserviceable and see to it that proper procedures were followed and necessary supporting documents are available for audit before any disposal of unserviceable property is undertaken.

We recommended that the Municipality properly dispose the unserviceable office furniture and equipment by undertaking the following procedures:
Prepare the required Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property for all the unserviceable office furniture and equipment junked in their storeroom; 
Conduct inspection of the unserviceable property, determine the manner of disposition and indicate the results thereof in the IIRUP; 
Determine the saleable value of the unserviceable properties, indicate these in the IIRUP; 
Publish the public auction and conduct the sale; and 
Upon disposal, the Municipal Accountant should draw Journal Entry Voucher to drop from the books the unserviceable properties.
